Author: DoubleGate <parobek@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Jun 2 00:10:48 2026 -0400

    feat(v2.0): $2007 PPU-DATA read-buffer + sprite-fetch de-collapse (24%->96%)
    
    Tier 1.3, behind default-OFF feature ppu-2007-read-buffer (nes-ppu ->
    nes-core -> nes-test-harness). Models the $2007-read-during-rendering
    PPU-DATA state machine: a $2007 read while the screen is drawn does NOT
    load data_buffer from VRAM[v] immediately; ~4 PPU cycles after the CPU
    read ends, the state machine's read step latches the value the
    background/sprite FETCH cadence reads at the landing dot (the fetch takes
    bus priority). Isolated — observable only on a $2007 read during
    rendering; the rendering / A12 / sprite-zero FSM is untouched.
    
    The BG fetch is already per-dot (fetch_nt/at/bg_lo/bg_hi @ phases
    1/3/5/7); this captures last_fetch_read there and de-collapses the
    257-320 sprite-tile fetch to its per-dot read cadence (two nametable
    reads in a row, then PT-lo/PT-hi from the raw pre-flip pattern bytes).
    A $2007 read-end during rendering schedules a deferred data_buffer latch
    (ppudata_sm_read_dot = dot + offset), consumed at the end of the per-dot
    fetch dispatch.
    
    $2007 Stress stable-read match: 24% -> 96% (164/170). The test is
    all-or-nothing (170/170 with alignment tolerance), so it still reports
    error 2; the residual 6 are real-hardware transition-cycle reads at the
    BG/sprite boundary + pre-fetch tail that NO emulator passes -- Mesen
    fails the whole test. Banked as validated infra; NOT promoted (does not
    pass yet).
    
    Gates (flag-on): AccuracyCoin 25 fail / 82.01% (no regression), 60-ROM
    commercial oracle 60/60 byte-identical, ppu_vbl_nmi 10/10,
    cpu_interrupts_v2 5/5, nes-ppu 41/41, clippy/fmt clean default+feature,
    no_std thumbv7em clean. Default build byte-identical (all cfg-gated).
    
    See docs/audit/v2.0-2007-stress-ppudata-2026-06-01.md.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

